        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Remark. This problem amounts to refuting a potential generalization of the Mean Value Theorem to bivariate functions. Many counterexamples are possible. Kent Merryfi eld suggests y sin(2πx), for which all four of the boundary integrals vanish; here the partial derivatives are 2πycos(2πx) and sin(2πx). Catalin Zara suggests x1/3y2/3. Qingchun Ren suggests xy(1 − y).",
        "bbox": [
