      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2009_Solutions_2009s_page_002_6",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "However, the only cases where s1 ≤ 1 are where all of the ei are 0, in which case k(G) = 0, or where ei = 1 for some i and ej = 0 for j ≠ i, in which case k(G) = (i − 1)2i + 1. The right side is a strictly increasing function of i which equals 1793 for i = 8 and 4097 for i = 9, so it can never equal 2009. This proves the claim.",
        "bbox": [
          0.12705882352941175,
